article.headline: Bradley 81, Evansville 76
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- Marcellus Sommerville had 18 points and seven rebounds as Bradley held off Evansville 81-76 in a Missouri Valley Conference matchup Saturday. Three other players posted double figures for Bradley (10-4, 3-3). Jeremy Crouch and Lawrence Wright had 17 apiece, while Tony Bennett added 15. Bradley trailed by a point at halftime after Evansville (9-6, 3-4) shot 7-of-12 from 3-point range. Both teams shot well from long range, with Bradley hitting 7-of-19 3-pointers to Evansville's 13-of-28 for the game. Forward Matt Webster led Evansville with 24 points, including four 3-pointers. Guard Kyle Anslinger added 13 points and guard Andre Burton had 10. Bradley snapped a two-game losing streak with the win.
